{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851111833,"sessionID":"ses_287087b03ffeyVD3nCcP1r3a2k","part":{"id":"prt_d78f98541001gpz2OEXV0cxt2b","messageID":"msg_d78f840a9001NQ8my0g7F07iiu","sessionID":"ses_287087b03ffeyVD3nCcP1r3a2k","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-d0a3f27fb83a4a039b3e28a64641d506","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-010/design.md","content":"# AR-010 — Router 会话管理 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-010 — Router 会话管理 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nThe Router module provides HTTP-based session routing for AgentCube sandboxes. It manages session lifecycle, routes incoming invocation requests to appropriate sandbox pods via reverse proxy, and handles JWT-based authentication for secure communication between Router and Workload Manager.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n│   Client SDK    │────▶│     Router      │────▶│  WorkloadMgr    │\n│ (Python/CLI)    │     │  (pkg/router)   │     │(pkg/workloadmgr)│\n└─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n                              │                         │\n                              │                         │\n                              ▼                         ▼\n                        ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n                        │   Session Store │     │   Kubernetes    │\n                        │ (Redis/Memory)  │     │   API Server    │\n                        └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Request Flow\n\n```\nClient Request (with x-agentcube-session-id header)\n       │\n       ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ 1. Concurrency Limit Middleware (semaphore channel)      │\n│    - Reject with 429 if max concurrent exceeded          │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n       │\n       ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ 2. Logging Middleware                                    │\n│    - Record request method, path, duration               │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n       │\n       ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ 3. Recovery Middleware                                   │\n│    - Panic recovery → 500 response                       │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n       │\n       ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ 4. handleInvoke (AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter)           │\n│    - Extract namespace, name, path from URL params       │\n│    - Get sessionID from x-agentcube-session-id header    │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n       │\n       ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ 5. SessionManager.GetSandboxBySession                    │\n│    - If sessionID empty → create new sandbox             │\n│    - If sessionID provided → lookup from store           │\n│    - On not found → SessionNotFoundError                 │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n       │\n       ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ 6. UpdateSessionLastActivity (before proxy)              │\n│    - Update LastActivity timestamp in store              │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n       │\n       ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ 7. Entry Point Selection                                 │\n│    - selectEntryPoint: prefix match or first entry       │\n│    - buildTargetURL: construct backend URL               │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n       │\n       ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ 8. JWT Generation (for Sandbox/SandboxClaim kinds)       │\n│    - JWTManager.GenerateToken with session claims        │\n│    - RS256 signing with RSA 2048-bit key                 │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n       │\n       ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ 9. Reverse Proxy                                         │\n│    - httputil.NewSingleHostReverseProxy                  │\n│    - Director: rewrite URL, add forwarding headers       │\n│    - ModifyResponse: set x-agentcube-session-id          │\n│    - ErrorHandler: connection refused → 502, timeout→504│\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n       │\n       ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ 10. UpdateSessionLastActivity (after proxy)              │\n│    - Update activity timestamp again                     │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### Component Relationships\n\n| Component | Role | Dependencies |\n|-----------|------|--------------|\n| `Server` | Gin HTTP server, route registration, graceful shutdown | `Config`, `SessionManager`, `Store`, `JWTManager`, `Logger` |\n| `sessionManager` | Session lookup, sandbox creation via Workload Manager | `Store`, `http.Client` (to WorkloadMgr) |\n| `JWTManager` | RS256 JWT token generation, key persistence | `rsa.PrivateKey`, Kubernetes client (optional) |\n| `ReverseProxyWrapper` | Request director, response modification, error handling | `url.URL`, JWT string |\n| `Store` (interface) | Session/sandbox CRUD, activity tracking | Redis or in-memory implementation |\n| `middleware.go` | Concurrency limiting, logging, panic recovery | `gin.Context`, `Logger` |\n| `errors.go` | Custom error types with APIStatus interface | None |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose | Import Path |\n|---------|---------|-------------|\n| Gin | HTTP router and middleware | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` |\n| JWT | JWT token generation and signing | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` |\n| HTTP2 | HTTP/2 transport configuration | `golang.org/x/net/http2` |\n| Kubernetes API | APIStatus error interface | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors` |\n| Klog | Logging | `k8s.io/klog/v2` |\n| Common Types | SandboxInfo, CreateSandboxRequest/Response | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` |\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Config (`config.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Port                  string  // Default \":8080\"\n    EnableTLS             bool    // TLS mode toggle\n    TLSCert               string  // TLS certificate file path\n    TLSKey                string  // TLS key file path\n    MaxConcurrentRequests int     // Semaphore size, default 1000\n    Debug                 bool    // Gin debug mode toggle\n}\n```\n\n### Server (`server.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    config         *Config\n    engine         *gin.Engine\n    httpServer     *http.Server\n    sessionManager SessionManager\n    storeClient    Store\n    httpTransport  *http.Transport\n    jwtManager     *JWTManager\n    logger         Logger\n}\n```\n\n### sessionManager (`session_manager.go`)\n\n```go\ntype sessionManager struct {\n    storeClient     Store\n    workloadMgrAddr string         // From WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env\n    httpClient      *http.Client   // Timeout: 2m, HTTP/2 enabled\n}\n```\n\n### JWTManager (`jwt.go`)\n\n```go\ntype JWTManager struct {\n    privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey  // 2048-bit RSA key\n    publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n}\n\nconst (\n    rsaKeySize         = 2048\n    jwtExpiration      = 5 * time.Minute\n    IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"\n    PrivateKeyDataKey  = \"private.pem\"\n    PublicKeyDataKey   = \"public.pem\"\n)\n\nvar IdentityNamespace = \"default\" // Overridden by AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE\n```\n\n### SandboxInfo (`pkg/common/types/sandbox.go`)\n\n```go\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    Kind               string\n    SandboxID          string\n    SandboxNamespace   string\n    SandboxName        string\n    Name               string\n    SessionID          string\n    CreatedAt          time.Time\n    ExpiresAt          time.Time\n    Status             string\n    EntryPoints        []SandboxEntryPoint\n    UserToken          string              // Optional\n    ServiceAccount     string              // Optional\n    ServiceAccountName string              // Optional\n    LastActivity       time.Time           // Optional\n}\n\ntype SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n    Path     string  // URL path prefix\n    Protocol string  // \"http\" or \"https\"\n    Endpoint string  // Backend host:port or full URL\n}\n```\n\n### ReverseProxyWrapper (`reverse_proxy.go`)\n\n```go\ntype ReverseProxyWrapper struct {\n    director       func(*http.Request)\n    modifyResponse func(*http.Response) error\n    errorHandler   func(http.ResponseWriter, *http.Request, error)\n}\n```\n\n### Interfaces (`doc.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n}\n\ntype Logger interface {\n    Info(msg string, keysAndValues ...any)\n    Error(msg string, keysAndValues ...any)\n    Warning(msg string, keysAndValues ...any)\n}\n\ntype SessionManager interface {\n    GetSandboxBySession(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, namespace string, name string, kind string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n\ntype APIStatus interface {\n    Status() int\n    Code() string\n    Message() string\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Route Table\n\n| Method | Path | Middleware | Handler |\n|--------|------|------------|---------|\n| GET | `/health/live` | none | `handleHealthLive` → `{\"status\":\"alive\"}` |\n| GET | `/health/ready` | none | `handleHealthReady` → `{\"status\":\"ready\"}` or 503 |\n| GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | concurrency, logging, recovery | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n| POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/agent-runtimes/:name/invocations/*path` | concurrency, logging, recovery | `handleAgentInvoke` |\n| GET | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | concurrency, logging, recovery | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n| POST | `/v1/namespaces/:namespace/code-interpreters/:name/invocations/*path` | concurrency, logging, recovery | `handleCodeInterpreterInvoke` |\n\n### Request Headers\n\n| Header | Required | Description |\n|--------|----------|-------------|\n| `x-agentcube-session-id` | No | Existing session ID for reuse; empty → new session creation |\n\n### Response Headers\n\n| Header | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `x-agentcube-session-id` | Session ID echoed back for client tracking |\n\n### Workload Manager API Calls\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Request Body | Response |\n|----------|--------|--------------|----------|\n| `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/agent-runtime` | POST | `CreateSandboxRequest{kind, name, namespace}` | `CreateSandboxResponse{sessionId, sandboxId, sandboxName, entryPoints}` |\n| `{WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL}/v1/code-interpreter` | POST | `CreateSandboxRequest{kind, name, namespace}` | `CreateSandboxResponse{sessionId, sandboxId, sandboxName, entryPoints}` |\n\n### JWT Claims Structure\n\n```json\n{\n  \"exp\": <unix timestamp + 5min>,\n  \"iat\": <unix timestamp>,\n  \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n  \"session_id\": \"<session ID>\",\n  \"sandbox_id\": \"<sandbox ID>\",\n  \"namespace\": \"<sandbox namespace>\",\n  \"name\": \"<sandbox name>\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Custom Error Types (`errors.go`)\n\n| Error Type | HTTP Status | Code | Message |\n|------------|-------------|------|---------|\n| `SessionNotFoundError` | 404 | `SESSION_NOT_FOUND` | \"session not found\" |\n| `SandboxUnreachableError` | 502 | `SANDBOX_UNREACHABLE` | \"sandbox unreachable\" |\n| `SandboxTimeoutError` | 504 | `SANDBOX_TIMEOUT` | \"sandbox timeout\" |\n| `JWTSigningError` | 500 | `JWT_SIGNING_FAILED` | \"jwt signing failed\" |\n| `ServerOverloadedError` | 429 | `SERVER_OVERLOADED` | \"server overloaded, please try again later\" |\n| `NoEntryPointError` | 404 | `NO_ENTRY_POINT` | \"no entry point configured\" |\n| `WorkloadManagerError` | Dynamic | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_ERROR` | Dynamic message |\n\n### Error Response Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"<message>\",\n  \"code\": \"<error code>\"\n}\n```\n\n### Error Handling Strategy\n\n1. **Session lookup errors**: Return `SessionNotFoundError` when session ID provided but not found in store\n2. **Workload Manager errors**: Wrap HTTP response errors in `WorkloadManagerError` with original status code\n3. **Proxy errors**: Detect \"connection refused\" → 502, \"timeout\" → 504 via string matching\n4. **Entry point errors**: Return 404 if no entry points configured or path prefix not matched\n5. **Concurrency limit**: Return 429 immediately when semaphore full (non-blocking)\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Test Coverage Goals\n\n| Component | Coverage Target | Key Test Cases |\n|-----------|-----------------|----------------|\n| `session_manager.go` | 90%+ | Existing session lookup, new sandbox creation, WorkloadMgr errors, unsupported kind, empty sessionID in response |\n| `server.go` | 85%+ | Route registration, health endpoints, concurrent request limiting, TLS validation, graceful shutdown |\n| `jwt.go` | 80%+ | Token generation, claim merging, RSA key creation, PEM encoding/decoding |\n| `reverse_proxy.go` | 85%+ | Entry point selection, URL building, proxy director, error handler classification |\n| `middleware.go` | 90%+ | Concurrency limit (accept/reject), logging capture, panic recovery |\n| `errors.go` | 100% | All error type methods (Error, Status, Code, Message) |\n\n### Test Patterns\n\n1. **Mock Store**: `MockStore` with function fields for flexible testing\n2. **Mock HTTP Client**: `httptest.Server` for Workload Manager simulation\n3. **Mock SessionManager**: `mockSessionManager` with configurable `getFunc`\n4. **Mock Logger**: `MockLogger` with Info/Error recording for middleware tests\n\n### Integration Test Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| Full request flow | Client → Router → mock WorkloadMgr → verify proxy headers |\n| Session reuse | Provide existing sessionID → verify no new sandbox created |\n| New session creation | Empty sessionID → verify POST to WorkloadMgr, store write |\n| TLS startup | EnableTLS=true with missing cert → verify error |\n| Graceful shutdown | Context cancellation → verify 10s timeout shutdown |\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` environment variable required for SessionManager initialization\n- [ ] Concurrency limit defaults to 1000 when `MaxConcurrentRequests <= 0`\n- [ ] JWT expires in 5 minutes, signed with RS256\n- [ ] Session activity updated before and after proxy for accurate idle tracking\n- [ ] Entry point selection uses prefix match, falls back to first entry\n- [ ] Proxy error classification based on error message content\n- [ ] Health check `/health/ready` returns 503 when SessionManager unavailable\n- [ ] Gin mode set to ReleaseMode when `config.Debug=false`\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. Should JWT key persistence be mandatory for production deployments (current implementation allows ephemeral keys)?\n2. Should proxy timeout be configurable per entry point (currently hardcoded in transport)?\n3. Should session creation be rate-limited independently from concurrent request limit?\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- `session-routing/design.md` — Session routing module design\n- `pkg/router/doc.go` — Interface definitions\n- `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` — SandboxInfo and request/response types\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_t